Dear sirs,
im trying to find out the best generic way of JUnit testing J2ee
applications.
That would mean testing EJBs, Servlets and JSP pages, as well as all the
&#39;normal&#39; beans and helper classes.
Although I&#39;ve found some guidelines to how such testing could be performed,
a lot of these promotes the usage of custom made &#39;fake&#39; application servers
and Request/Response wrappers for the Servlet testing. This feels extremely
heavy..
Is there a recommended approach that someone had good results with?
Im thinking in the lines of having all the test cases in a separate WAR or
EAR, and maybee incorporate log4j to simplify the testing.

But using printing to log4j as a result source would give the production
code a unwanted overhead as well as be a very ugly way of conduct.

Please, if you&#39;ve got a good design for JUnit testing in the J2EE
environment, share it with me.

WR

